<item>
            <title>[JDK-8302558] Editable JComboBox&apos;s popup blocks user from seeing characters in Aqua look and feel</title>
                <link>https://bugs.openjdk.org/browse/JDK-8302558</link>
                <project id="10100" key="JDK">JDK</project>
                    <description>Test Scenario : Type characters into editable JComboBox.&lt;br/&gt;
Step to reproduce:&lt;br/&gt;
1) Run the attached test &lt;br/&gt;
2) When the frame is visible. Click on the JComboBox which has the Title border. Observe that JComboBox popup is visible. &lt;br/&gt;
3) I was expecting the popup to be visible below the Editable JComboBox textfield but popup is seen above the editable JComboBox textfield.&lt;br/&gt;
4) Try typing characters into the editable JComboBox textfield . You will not the see the character that is getting typed since popup blocks the user  from seeing. &lt;br/&gt;
If you observe the same then the bug is reproduced.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
This does happen when editable JComboBox with out titleBorder or border set.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
This works fine in Java Look and feel&lt;br/&gt;
</description>
